### Build-a-Bank · Step 14 · API Design — versioning, idempotency, pagination & webhooks
### 1) Postgres:  docker compose -f services/demand-account/compose.yaml up -d   (maps host 5433)
### 2) Service (optionally point webhooks at a receiver like https://webhook.site):
###    SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/demand_account \
###    BANK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://webhook.site/your-id BANK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_demo \
###    ./mvnw -pl services/demand-account spring-boot:run

@host = http://localhost:8082

### Open accounts
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-A","currency":"USD","openingBalance":200.00}

###
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-B","currency":"USD","openingBalance":0.00}

### v1 transfer WITH an idempotency key → 200. Send this TWICE with the SAME key:
### the money moves only once and you get the same transactionId back. (Also fires a signed webhook.)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/transfers
Idempotency-Key: demo-key-001
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":50.00,"description":"rent"}

### Confirm A only dropped by 50 (to 150), even if you sent the above twice
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/ACC-A

### v1 paginated ledger entries for A → a PageResponse {content,page,size,totalElements,totalPages}
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts/ACC-A/entries?page=0&size=2&sort=createdAt,desc

### The DEPRECATED transfer endpoint still works but returns Deprecation / Sunset / Link headers
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":1.00}

### Webhook receivers verify our signature like this (pseudocode):
###   expected = hmac_sha256(secret, "<X-Webhook-Timestamp>." + rawBody)
###   reject if expected != X-Webhook-Signature  OR  abs(now - timestamp) > 300s   (replay protection)
